import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['distance'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='r', label=f'Median: {data["distance"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.groupby('origin')['date'].count().sort_values(ascending=False).head(20).plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Airport Code')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
